HONG MUN WAY, Appellant, v. John D. NAGLE, Commissioner of Immigration, Port of San Francisco, Appellee. No. 6527. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 12, 1931.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and JAMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to oral motion of counsel for appellant, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
